  "stem": "<p>The function <i>h</i> is defined by <i>h</i>(<i>x</i>) = |<i>x</i>|/<i>b</i> &minus; 9, where <i>b</i> &lt; 0. What is the product of <i>h</i>(12<i>b</i>) and <i>h</i>(6<i>b</i>)?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "315"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Since <i>b</i> &lt; 0, |12<i>b</i>| = &minus;12<i>b</i> and |6<i>b</i>| = &minus;6<i>b</i>. Then <i>h</i>(12<i>b</i>) = (&minus;12<i>b</i>)/<i>b</i> &minus; 9 = &minus;12 &minus; 9 = &minus;21. And <i>h</i>(6<i>b</i>) = (&minus;6<i>b</i>)/<i>b</i> &minus; 9 = &minus;6 &minus; 9 = &minus;15. Product = (&minus;21)(&minus;15) = 315.</p>",
